<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/45407455-linnea-kroeger"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1491526920i/45407455._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/45407455-linnea-kroeger">Linnea Kroeger</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No, you do not have to read the previous book to read this one, each chapter is a different story. However, you do get to know the characters better i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No, you do not have to read the previous book to read this one, each chapter is a different story. However, you do get to know the characters better if you read it in order.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
