<span id="freeTextContainer3134003203983949577">The second of Herriot&apos;s wonderful memoirs of his veterinary practice in mid-twentieth century Yorkshire. As with <i>All Creatures Great and Small</i>, his love for the place, the people, and the critters is palpable on every page. Recommended for everyone, especially animal lovers and Anglophiles. But be warned - some of the medical procedures are pretty gruesome.</span>
  <span id="freeText3134003203983949577" style="display:none">The second of Herriot's wonderful memoirs of his veterinary practice in mid-twentieth century Yorkshire. As with <i>All Creatures Great and Small</i>, his love for the place, the people, and the critters is palpable on every page. Recommended for everyone, especially animal lovers and Anglophiles. But be warned - some of the medical procedures are pretty gruesome.</span>
